claim.claim-text:
1. A method of assembling a packaged high frequency circuit module including the steps of:
providing a ceramic substrate;
firing the ceramic substrate; to form one or more elongate stub walls projecting from a planar surface of the substrate
processing the fired substrate until the planar surface of the one or more elongate stub walls is uniform and parallel;
applying a conductive adhesive to the processed surfaces of the one or more stub walls; and
placing a housing lid over the substrate, the lid having one or more members projecting from a planar surface thereof so that the one or more members align with the one or more stub walls of the substrate to form a composite structure.
